    "Body": " Industrial, Human Factors and Usability Designer Avanos - 3.5 Alpharetta, GA Apply Now Job Details CommissionEstimated: $67,000 - $93,000 a year Benefits Health Insurance 401(k) Matching Life Insurance On-site Gym 401(k) Qualifications FDA Regulations Usability Communication Skills Adobe Photoshop Research & Development Master's Degree Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description Requisition ID: 2004 Job Title: Industrial, Human Factors and Usability Designer Job Country: United States (US) Here at Avanos Medical, we passionately believe in three things: Making a difference in our products, services and offers, never ceasing to fight for groundbreaking solutions in everything we do; Making a difference in how we work and collaborate, constantly nurturing our nimble culture of innovation; Having an impact on the healthcare challenges we all face, and the lives of people and communities around the world. At Avanos you will find an environment that strives to be independent and different, one that supports and inspires you to excel and to help change what medical devices can deliver, now and in the future. Avanos is a medical device company focused on delivering clinically superior breakthrough solutions that will help patients get back to the things that matter. We are committed to creating the next generation of innovative healthcare solutions which will address our most important healthcare needs, such as reducing the use of opioids while helping patients move from surgery to recovery. Headquartered in Alpharetta, Georgia, we develop, manufacture and market recognized brands in more than 90 countries. Avanos Medical is traded on the New York Stock Exchange under the ticker symbol AVNS. For more information, visit www.avanos.com . The role This position is part of the Global Design Services Team chartered with supporting the R&D, Quality, and Regulatory teams to help design, evaluate, and document how product solutions create a safe, optimized, confident, and satisfying user experience. This team is a global capability supporting initiatives in all of Avanos\u2019 product portfolios in Respiratory Health, Digestive Health, and Pain Management, and Neuromodulation. This position is in the Atlanta area in Alpharetta, Georgia. Essential Duties and Responsibilities: Establish Subject Matter Expert role and technical leadership in Industrial Design. Provide leadership on appropriate activities and scaling the deployment of usability engineering planning for project teams. Provide expertise to R&D and the Global Design team on best practices, heuristics, and established ergonomic data to provide design inputs to iterative design solutions. Support of Formative Evaluations and Summative Validations as needed. Identify use errors and difficulties and provide support in evaluation of root cause analyses. Support technical quality teams to advise and collaborate during use/task based risk assessments and support usability components of risk management file. Provide support for development of User Interface Requirements. Support team leadership with educating and training Avanos organization team members on Human Centered Design process Support development of documentation for Usability Engineering File and HFE Report for submissions. Your qualifications Required: Minimum Master\u2019s degree in Industrial or Product Design or equivalent and 4-6+ years of experience or Bachelor\u2019s Degree in Industrial or Product Design or equivalent and 8-10+ years of experience Minimum 4 years of experience in design and evaluation of user interfaces, GUI development, UX engineering, medical device product design, product design, or equivalents Creative thinker, demonstrated expertise in problem solving in the aspect of development of user interfaces and enhancement of risk control measures Solid verbal and written communication skills Proven collaboration with cross-functional / multi-disciplinary teams Solidworks, Illustrator, and PhotoShop experience required Strong working knowledge of Human Factor usability principals Ability to travel up to 25% at times, potentially some international. Preferred: Previous medical device industry experience preferred Familiar with 62366, HE 75 and FDA Guidance for Human Factors and Usability Avanos Medical is an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other characteristic protected by law. If you are a current employee of Avanos, please apply here . Join us at Avanos Join us and you can make a difference in our products, solutions and our culture. Most of all, you can make a difference in the lives, people, and communities around the world. Make your career count Our commitment to improving the health and wellbeing of others begins with our employees \u2013 through a comprehensive and competitive range of benefits. We provide more than just a salary \u2013 our Total Rewards package encompasses everything you receive as an employee; your pay, health care benefits, retirement plans and work/life benefits. free onsite gym | onsite cafeteria | 401(k) + 6% match | immediate vesting | benefits on day 1 | uncapped sales commissions | HQ region voted \u2018best place to live\u2019 by USA Today "
